## Dependencies

Make sure these are installed before using the project:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en)
- [Just](https://github.com/casey/just)
- [mcbe](https://github.com/Paperweightt/oxidized_copper)
- Minecraft Bedrock Edition

You will also need:

- PowerShell (Windows)

## Setup

Install project dependencies:

```powershell
npm install
```

## Available Commands

### Build

Builds the addon using esbuild:

```powershell
just build
```

### Watch Mode

Automatically rebuilds on file changes:

```powershell
just build-watch
```

### Link Addon to Minecraft

Creates development links for the behavior and resource packs:

```powershell
just link
```

### Unlink Addon

Removes development links from Minecraft:

```powershell
just unlink
```

### Bump Manifest Version

Updates the manifest version for both packs:

```powershell
just bump patch
just bump minor
just bump major
```

## Notes

- The project is configured for Windows.
- Paths target the Minecraft Bedrock development pack directories inside `%USERPROFILE%/AppData/Roaming`.
- The build pipeline uses `esbuild.config.mjs`.
